did.abstract: The videotapes in this collection, produced by the Office of Media Production, include promotional material, commencement footage and documentary footage of speakers, visitors and events. The tapes range in date from 1983-2007.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The video material is arranged by project number within each box or set of boxes.
The tapes are grouped into one series.

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Material
separatedmaterial.p: There is no information about materials that are associated by provenance to the described materials that have been physically separated or removed.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The videotapes in this collection include promotional material, news and documentary footage, as well as recordings of different speakers and events at NYU. The tapes comprise approximately 500 projects produced by the Office of Media Production.

bioghist.head: History of the Office of Media Production
bioghist.p: This collection contains videotapes produced by the Office of Media Production from 1983-2007.

The Office of Media Production was established to "create digital communication strategies to advance recruitment, development and public relations." It consults on, conceives and produces video content for departments and schools for a variety of purposes. The office began in an informal capacity when Elisa Guarino began producing video works for the Office of the Vice President of External Affairs in the early 1980s. It became an official University operation around 1987 and remained under External Affairs until NYU President John Sexton later brought that department under the auspices of the Office of University Relations and Public Affairs, which "is responsible for ensuring that NYU's message, agenda, and image are effectively and creatively projected to both external and internal audiences."

Guarino continues to run the department. Based on the project titles in the online finding aid, the collection contains promotional productions, University commencement ceremonies, lectures, panel discussions, and other events as well as B-roll footage of the NYU campus, study abroad sites and other New York City locations.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); The Office of Media Production Videotapes; RG 7.3.4; box number; New York University Archives.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Permission to publish materials must be obtained in writing from the: New York University Archives, Elmer Holmes Bobst Library, 70 Washington Square South, New York, NY 10012 Phone: (212) 998-2641 Fax: (212) 995-4225 E-mail: university.archives@library.nyu.edu

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p:
Some restrictions may apply. This collection is in
off-site storage .

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: The videotapes in this collection were transferred in multiple accessions to the University Archives by the Office of Media Production, formerly under the authority of the Senior Vice President for External Affairs and presently reporting to the Senior Vice President for University Relations and Public Affairs.
